# Fleet-wide config — group_vars/all.yml
#
# Values here apply to EVERY server in this fleet. This file belongs in YOUR FLEET
# repo (next to inventory.ini and host_vars/), copied from this example — NOT in the
# miuops tool checkout: Ansible loads tool-adjacent group_vars at higher precedence
# than the fleet's, so `miuops apply` refuses to converge if it finds group_vars in
# the tool dir (the same fail-closed guard as host_vars).
#
# Per-server values go in host_vars/<server>.yml; values shared by the whole fleet
# go here. (group_vars/all.yml itself is gitignored in this repo so a local copy in
# the tool checkout is never committed; commit it in your fleet repo instead.)

# --- Grafana Cloud observability (shared by the whole fleet) -------------------
# The push endpoints + user IDs are CONFIG (not secret) and identical across servers,
# so they live here — versioned, never via per-apply env. When observability_enabled is
# true the role REQUIRES all four (it asserts they are non-empty, failing the converge
# LOUD if one is missing). Uncomment and fill:
# observability_enabled: true
# grafana_cloud_prometheus_url:  "https://prometheus-prod-XX.grafana.net/api/prom/push"
# grafana_cloud_prometheus_user: "1234567"
# grafana_cloud_loki_url:        "https://logs-prod-XX.grafana.net/loki/api/v1/push"
# grafana_cloud_loki_user:       "1234567"
#
# The TOKEN is a SECRET — it does NOT go here. It bridges via the environment
# (export GRAFANA_CLOUD_TOKEN) until the SOPS-encrypted fleet secret supplies it.

# --- Backup destination (shared by the whole fleet) ---------------------------
# One S3 bucket for the whole fleet; each server backs up under its own <server>/
# prefix with its own scoped IAM key. The bucket name, client-side encryption mode,
# and age recipients are CONFIG, identical across servers, so they live here once
# (single source of truth) — `miuops backup-setup` reads the bucket from here and never
# asks you to re-type it. The per-server AWS key is a SECRET that `miuops backup-setup`
# writes into fleet/secrets/<server>.vars.json (SOPS); it is NOT set here. Uncomment:
# backup_s3_bucket: "your-fleet-backup"
# backup_encryption: age          # none | age (client-side encryption before upload)
# backup_age_recipients:
#   - "age1..."                   # or ssh-ed25519 / age1yubikey1... (decrypt-side key)
